{
  "text": "An important question remains on the relationship between immunological perturbations and physical functioning. This study examined whether these associations could be identified, using simple, validated measures of physical status [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and is the first to examine this using these immune parameters. Among healthy controls, lower NK cell activity was associated with poorer physical status. Though this was not observed among CFS/ME patients, the findings to support that lower NK cell activity in general may be a sign of poor health. As CFS/ ME patients are shown to have significantly lower NK cell activity than healthy controls, this may continue to be a reliable indicator of their illness.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22018679",
